Pre-Game Insights: Denmark's manager Kasper Hjulmand emphasized the importance of building momentum ahead of the Euro 2024 tournament.
Sweden's new coach Jon Dahl Tomasson aims to disrupt Denmark's preparations with a strong performance.
Rasmus Hojlund's ability to hold play and assist in building from the back is a key strength for Denmark.
Alexander Isak's versatility and goal-scoring ability are crucial for Sweden's attack.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match is the first for Sweden under their new manager Jon Dahl Tomasson.
Denmark has a strong home record against Sweden, with most matches ending in a 1-0 scoreline.
The match will be telecast in India on Sony Sports Network and Sony Liv.
